latestPosts.caption:
I refuse to burn out 😤

Ok in reality, I have felt really disconnected from my content lately, so I want to personally share with you all of the behind the scenes of who is behind this account. 😇

My journey with social media this year has been a wild one, and it’s crazy that 40k+ of you found something special in me and that means the world to me. 🥺❤️🫶

While I’ve been able to consistently keep up #timefortailoringtuesday because it is my small business, my goal is to get back on track with #sewsomethingsunday because those are usually more fun & personal projects. 🪡

I have even bigger goals for 2025, and I’m using the rest of this year to get my life together and possibly find some balance. 😅

-

latestPosts.caption:
If you don’t have a large selection of fabrics local to where you are, @beglarianfabrics has such a beautiful selection of designer dead stock fabrics! 

I purposely got fabrics that had small defects on them (which are disclosed in the descriptions) because they’re discounted, and I can work around them. ❤️‍🩹

Fabrics were kindly gifted to me. 

⭐️ use code Angela20 for 20% off your order!

This is how to make your button-up shirt more fitted at the waist if it doesn’t have any waist darts! 
The most important thing here is making sure you have a nice blend to zero from the waist to the armhole and from the waist to the hemline. That’s it!

-

#timefortailoringtuesday #howtotakeinashirt #howtotailorashirt #beginnersewingtutorial #upcycledfashiondesign #thriftflip #diysewing #alterations #seamstress #phillytailor #sewists

I honestly didn’t feel the need to download patterns until I found @sewingwithjenn she makes the cutest designs that are feminine and trendy!!! 🌟

I ended up using georgette for the fabric, since the double layer would help disguise any sheerness. It came out super flowy and flouncy! 

If you’re a beginner sewist, I recommend sewing this pattern with a cotton poplin so it’s a bit easier to work with and has that classic cottage-core vibe. :)

-

#sewsomethingsunday #patterntesting #patterndigitaldownload #sewingtutorial #skort

If you have the problem of constantly adjusting the shoulders on your tops/dresses, it’s because the balance of the neckline from the front to back is not balanced to your proportions. This is often more of a design issue and not a you issue (but if you have broader shoulders, it is easier for you to wear open necklines like these!)

I made my ties from scratch from bias strips, but you can easily just buy trim/ribbon, and it’s as simple as sewing the ends to each side of the back neck opening. 

-

This is the reality of what it’s like trying to build something while you work a full time job—adulting is really hard!!! 🥺

If any of y’all are curious,
I started my LLC with @tailor 
I opened my business bank acc with @bankwithrelay 
I got my business CC with @americanexpressbusiness 
I set up my booking site with @square

I’m locked back in 😤

But seriously, thanks for sticking with me while I was on hiatus from posting sewing content — I really needed time to reevaluate my priorities and catch up on life. I’m finally in a better place mentally and physically than where I was at ~ 2 months ago (wow time flies) 😌

I was running on empty for too long. I’ve finally gotten the chance to recharge and I’m ready to create again. 🦋
Bali healed me last month 🐌
